---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Daoist Philosophy" description="Discover Daoist philosophy - the wisdom of Laozi, Zhuangzi, yin-yang theory, and China's spiritual heritage">
  
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="relative h-[70vh] flex items-center overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0">
      <img
        src="/images/tai-chi.jpg"
        alt="Yin Yang symbol"
        class="w-full h-full object-cover"
      />
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-[#1a1a1a]/95 to-[#8E4585]/60"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="relative max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-2xl">
        <span class="inline-block font-heading text-sm tracking-[0.3em] text-[#D4AF37] mb-4">PHILOSOPHY</span>
        <h1 class="font-display text-5xl md:text-6xl text-white mb-6">Daoist Philosophy</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-stone-300 leading-relaxed">
          The wisdom of Laozi, the poetry of Zhuangzi, and the eternal dance of yin and yang. Discover China's spiritual heart.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Introduction -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-[#FFFEF7]">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center mb-20">
        <div>
          <span class="inline-block font-heading text-sm tracking-[0.3em] text-[#C41E3A] mb-4">THE WAY</span>
          <h2 class="font-display text-4xl text-[#1a1a1a] mb-6">What is Daoism?</h2>
          <p class="text-lg text-stone-600 mb-6">
            Daoism (道教, Dàojiào) is both a philosophy and a religion that emerged in ancient China. At its core is the concept of the Dao (道) — "The Way" — an ineffable force that underlies all existence.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-stone-600 mb-6">
            Daoism teaches harmony with nature, spontaneity, and non-action (无为, wúwéi) — not doing nothing, but doing what comes naturally without forcing outcomes.
          </p>
          <div class="p-6 bg-[#8E4585]/5 rounded-xl border-l-4 border-[#8E4585]">
            <p class="font-display text-xl italic text-[#1a1a1a]">
              "The Tao that can be told is not the eternal Tao."
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-stone-500 mt-2">— Laozi, Tao Te Ching</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="relative">
          <img
            src="/images/daoist-mountain.jpg"
            alt="Chinese landscape"
            class="rounded-xl shadow-2xl"
          />
          <div class="absolute -bottom-6 -left-6 bg-[#8E4585] text-white p-6 rounded-lg">
            <div class="stat-number text-3xl mb-1">道</div>
            <div class="text-sm tracking-wide">The Way</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Core Concepts -->
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        {[
          {
            concept: 'Wu Wei (无为)',
            desc: 'Non-action or effortless action. Not passive resignation, but acting in harmony with the natural flow of the Dao.',
            practice: 'Meditation, letting go, accepting what is'
          },
          {
            concept: 'Ziran (自然)',
            desc: 'Naturalness, spontaneity. Being true to one\'s own nature without artificiality or pretense.',
            practice: 'Simple living, authentic expression'
          },
          {
            concept: 'Pu (朴)',
            desc: 'The uncarved block. Simplicity and purity before social conventions shape us.',
            practice: 'Returning to simplicity, uncluttering life'
          },
          {
            concept: 'De (德)',
            desc: 'Virtue or power. The cultivation of inner virtue that naturally radiates outward.',
            practice: 'Self-cultivation, ethical living'
          }
        ].map(item => (
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg p-8">
            <h3 class="font-display text-2xl text-[#8E4585] mb-4">{item.concept}</h3>
            <p class="text-stone-600 mb-4">{item.desc}</p>
            <div class="pt-4 border-t border-stone-100">
              <span class="text-sm text-stone-500">Modern practice: </span>
              <span class="text-sm text-[#1a1a1a]">{item.practice}</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Yin Yang Section -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-[#1a1a1a]">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <span class="inline-block font-heading text-sm tracking-[0.3em] text-[#D4AF37] mb-4">SYMBOLISM</span>
        <h2 class="font-display text-4xl text-white mb-4">Yin and Yang</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-400 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          The yin-yang symbol (太极图) represents the fundamental Chinese understanding of reality: complementary opposites that interpenetrate and transform into each other.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
        <div class="flex justify-center">
          <div class="relative w-72 h-72">
            <!-- Yin-Yang SVG -->
            <svg viewBox="0 0 200 200" class="w-full h-full">
              <circle cx="100" cy="100" r="95" fill="#FFFEF7" stroke="#D4AF37" stroke-width="2"/>
              <path d="M100,5 A95,95 0 0,1 100,195 A47.5,47.5 0 0,1 100,100 A47.5,47.5 0 0,0 100,5" fill="#1a1a1a"/>
              <circle cx="100" cy="47.5" r="10" fill="#FFFEF7"/>
              <circle cx="100" cy="152.5" r="10" fill="#1a1a1a"/>
              <circle cx="100" cy="47.5" r="3" fill="#1a1a1a"/>
              <circle cx="100" cy="152.5" r="3" fill="#FFFEF7"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <div class="p-6 bg-stone-800/50 rounded-xl">
              <h4 class="font-display text-lg text-white mb-2">Yin (阴)</h4>
              <p class="text-stone-400 text-sm">Dark, receptive, feminine</p>
              <div class="mt-3 text-xs text-stone-500">
                <span class="inline-block px-2 py-1 bg-stone-700 rounded mr-1">Night</span>
                <span class="inline-block px-2 py-1 bg-stone-700 rounded mr-1">Moon</span>
                <span class="inline-block px-2 py-1 bg-stone-700 rounded">Water</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="p-6 bg-stone-800/50 rounded-xl">
              <h4 class="font-display text-lg text-white mb-2">Yang (阳)</h4>
              <p class="text-stone-400 text-sm">Light, active, masculine</p>
              <div class="mt-3 text-xs text-stone-500">
                <span class="inline-block px-2 py-1 bg-stone-700 rounded mr-1">Day</span>
                <span class="inline-block px-2 py-1 bg-stone-700 rounded mr-1">Sun</span>
                <span class="inline-block px-2 py-1 bg-stone-700 rounded">Fire</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="p-6 bg-[#8E4585]/20 rounded-xl border border-[#8E4585]/30">
            <p class="text-stone-300 text-sm leading-relaxed">
              The core principle: <em>yin contains the seed of yang, and yang contains the seed of yin.</em> Nothing is purely one or the other. Health comes from balance; imbalance creates disease. This wisdom applies to body, mind, and society.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Key Texts -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-[#FFFEF7]">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h2 class="font-display text-3xl text-[#1a1a1a] mb-4">Foundational Texts</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg p-8">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4 mb-4">
            <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-[#8E4585]/20 flex items-center justify-center text-2xl">📜</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-display text-2xl text-[#1a1a1a]">Tao Te Ching</h3>
              <span class="text-[#8E4585] text-sm">道德经</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-stone-600 mb-4">
            Attributed to the legendary figure Laozi, this 81-chapter text is the foundational scripture of Daoism. Its poetic verses explore the nature of the Dao, the art of leadership, and the path of wisdom.
          </p>
          <blockquote class="p-4 bg-stone-50 rounded-lg italic text-stone-700 text-sm">
            "When the great Dao is forgotten, benevolence and righteousness arise."
          </blockquote>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg p-8">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4 mb-4">
            <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-[#00A86B]/20 flex items-center justify-center text-2xl">📚</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-display text-2xl text-[#1a1a1a]">Zhuangzi</h3>
              <span class="text-[#00A86B] text-sm">庄子</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-stone-600 mb-4">
            The most important Daoist text after the Tao Te Ching. Zhuangzi's witty, paradoxical stories explore freedom, spontaneity, and the limitations of human understanding.
          </p>
          <blockquote class="p-4 bg-stone-50 rounded-lg italic text-stone-700 text-sm">
            "The fish trap exists because of the fish. Once you've gotten the fish you can forget the trap."
          </blockquote>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-gradient-to-r from-[#8E4585] to-[#1a1a1a]">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 text-center">
      <div class="text-6xl mb-6">☯️</div>
      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl text-white mb-4">Begin Your Practice</h2>
      <p class="text-white/80 text-lg mb-8">
        Daoism offers timeless wisdom for modern life. Start with stillness.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4">
        <a href="/" class="px-6 py-3 bg-white text-[#8E4585] font-semibold rounded-lg hover:bg-stone-100 transition-colors">
          Back to Home
        </a>
        <a href="/martial" class="px-6 py-3 border border-white text-white font-semibold rounded-lg hover:bg-white/10 transition-colors">
          Explore Martial Arts
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
